==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stake-driver
<hw>Stake"-driv`er</hw> <pr>(-dr⟦imac⟧v`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The common American bittern (<spn>Botaurus
lentiginosus</spn>); -- so called because one of its notes resembles the
sound made in driving a stake into the mud. Called also <altname>meadow
hen</altname>, and <altname>Indian hen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stakehead</ent>⟦br⟧
